title.narrative: HEALTH SYSTEMS, POLICY, RESEA

description.narrative: The government has a strengthened political commitment, accountability and national capacity for policy development, programming and evidence/ information generation for scaling-up maternal and child health interventions for children, adolescents and women of child bearing age by 2018, which contributes to Child Health, Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved and equitable use of high-impact maternal and child health intervention from pregnancy to adolescence and promotion of health behaviours

description.narrative: UNICEF's support contributed to improving data generation through Health Management Information System (HMIS) strengthening, with improved maternal and child health data quality, report completeness and timeliness observed from districts. Use of RapidPro and U-Report in monitoring of vaccine stock, drugs and medical commodity distribution, and electronic Integrated Disease Surveillance and Response data submission to the District Health Information System (DHIS2) platform enhanced monitoring and accountability of various Ministry of Health and Sanitation's programmes, demonstrating political commitment to developing national capacity. | Status:Met | As-of Date:05/02/2020
